I played this out, and if he goes to the corner, which seems like the obvious thing to do, I have a good attack.  Ironically, this wouldn't have worked if he'd moved Kf1, which seems like the more dangerous position because of the rook.  But Kf1 would have been more problematic for me.  Kh1 makes him more vulnerable, because all I need to do is get a power piece on the back rank, and he's done.  His other rook is stuck, and as long as I keep pressure on him, he won't be able to get the knight out.
